                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the donor; a few lines on the incipit page of Text I, alternating with black lines; two initial lines of Text II; two initial lines of each section of the text; names of Hebrew letters in Ps. 118 (fol. 39va); parts of abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic numerals or their elements; some other words, e.g., halle luya (e.g., fols. 2vb, 3ra, 4rb), wä-kaʿǝbä (e.g., fols. 7rb, 8vb, 9ra), ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 7rb, 8ra, 13va), nǝbäl (fols. 7va, 8rb), wä-yǝbälu (fols. 12va, 16va), ʾǝgäle (e.g., fols. 21ra, 38ra, 46rb), qǝdmä (e.g., fols. 31rb, 32va, 36vb), wä-ʾǝmzǝ (e.g, fols. 33va, 35va, 36vb).</rubric>
